00:21:00,301 --> 00:21:02,302
When we talked about demand last week,

309
00:21:03,063 --> 00:21:07,146
We said that for most products, when the price goes up, people buy less of the products.

310
00:21:07,226 --> 00:21:17,635
But there are a few products where there's not an easy substitute so that when the price goes up, people may buy a little less of it, but they will keep buying the product in elastic demand.

311
00:21:18,235 --> 00:21:19,016
That's exactly right.

312
00:21:19,396 --> 00:21:23,940
The amount by which high prices scare people away is not very much.

313
00:21:24,320 --> 00:21:25,361
That's what inelastic means.

314
00:21:25,814 --> 00:21:31,578
And if you can find something with inelastic demand, I mean, that is a very good business opportunity.

315
00:21:31,838 --> 00:21:38,482
That's the good news for Mr. Ross, which is he can bump up his price of a fair bit and he's not going to lose many customers.

